          "date": "2025-07-29 23:17:11+00:00",
          "body": "<html>\r\n<head>\r\n<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\">\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n<div class=\"yahoo-style-wrap\" style=\"font-family:arial;font-size:16px;\">\r\n<div dir=\"ltr\" data-setdir=\"false\">Greetings, I personally find a number of your attestations troubling. If you are a long time board member why didnt you assist in the previous attempts to oust Lapierre? There were some strong attempts to stop his stealing\r\n from the general funds and enriching himself and his cronies. The NRA used to be a viable organization but now its not on the political landscape. As soon as the NRA was turned into an arm of the Republican party it lost its clout. if you need me to remind\r\n you of all the foolish donations made by the NRA let me know. The NRA should be about gun ownership and the second amendment. the NRA should have 50 million plus members but you make it political. Democrats cannot attack the NRA if they have 10 mil plus members.\r\n You claim 20 to 30 mil claim to be NRA members but thats a pipe dream,. true membersiip is probably LESS THAN 3 MIL. Im a patriot life member at the benefactor level and have not gave 1 cent for years. When the NRA takes Lapierre to court for malfeasance and\r\n sues him and his cronies for stolen funds and gets rid of the crooked boards members than i might consider contributing again. In case your wondering im not a democrat or a republican. to flourish this organization needs to be apolitical. W. Glover</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n"
