          "date": "2025-07-28 19:57:15+00:00",
          "body": "To:  William A. Bachenberg, President\r\n\r\n-----Original Message-----\r\nFrom: 49715@reagan.com\r\nSent: Monday, July 28, 2025 3:55pm\r\nTo: president@nradirector.com\r\nSubject: FW: RE: NRA Jacket\r\n\r\nDoug Hamlin,\r\n\r\nI am a Patriot Life Member of the NRA (Patron Level).  My husband, Anthony Kaufman is a Patriot Life Member, Benefactor Level.\r\n\r\nI purchased an NRA Jacket for him back in January 2025.  For reasons I do not know, I still have not received the jacket.  I paid the $250.00.  NRA cashed my check.  But still I have no jacket.. I am told time and again, that 1)the jacket is hanging in my office.  2) that the jacket will be mailed in 3-4 weeks. That was in early June 25...still no jacket.\r\n\r\nCan you please assist me in receiving the jacket?\r\n\r\nIs there really a jacket?\r\n\r\nThank you,\r\n\r\nCarolyn Kaufman\r\n321-414-2796 Home phone number\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n-----Original Message-----\r\nFrom: 49715@reagan.com\r\nSent: Wednesday, June 11, 2025 11:16am\r\nTo: \"Cate, Devin\" <DCate@nrahq.org>\r\nSubject: RE: NRA Jacket\r\n\r\n\r\nOK, sorry to bother you.\r\nThank you so much,\r\nThe Kaufmans\r\n \r\n \r\n-----Original Message-----\r\nFrom: \"Cate, Devin\" <DCate@nrahq.org>\r\nSent: Wednesday, June 11, 2025 11:04am\r\nTo: \"49715@reagan.com\" <49715@reagan.com>\r\nSubject: RE: NRA Jacket\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nGood morning,\r\n \r\nThere’s no problem. It takes about 3-4 weeks from when we received the check for the jacket to arrive, so it will be another week or two.\r\n \r\nThank you,\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[  ]( https://linkprotect.cudasvc.com/url?a=https%3a%2f%2fhome.nra.org%2f&c=E,1,EBSsmu4yhDQSI9Aro4_SKODr6x1Q5NTajWHUkwcBsRWuZhlCV6L4ZZPCSSfrxb1lK2emAqCrc7hQdosZ0K-QN6k6tSjdNfRVYLdF6MIqm-aQnyHYFwf4SE_qPCs,&typo=1 )\r\nDevin Cate\r\nManager, Member Services\r\n Membership Division\r\nT (703) 397-3897\r\nE [ dcate@nrahq.org ]( mailto:dcate@nrahq.org )\r\n \r\n\r\nNational Rifle Association | 11250 Waples Mill Rd, Fairfax, VA 22030\r\n\r\n\r\n    [  ]( https://linkprotect.cudasvc.com/url?a=https%3a%2f%2fmembership.nra.org%2frecruiters%2fjoin%2fXR042902&c=E,1,mN_mWp5DMXep2EwktyIU16cYoeJ500a2KcLEgyfgFNksTVrzZgn9-nHcqDZ96jGSKocI3ExM8KIZuFHDXXOL3Onnjvr29k8WYaHtVehu&typo=1 )       \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThis e-mail and any files transmitted with it are confidential and intended solely for the use of the individual or entity to whom they are addressed.\r\n If you have received this e-mail in error, please notify the sender immediately, delete the message from your computer, and do not forward it.\r\n \r\n \r\n\r\nFrom: 49715@reagan.com <49715@reagan.com> \r\nSent: Wednesday, June 11, 2025 10:59 AM\r\nTo: Cate, Devin <DCate@nrahq.org>\r\nSubject: FW: NRA Jacket\r\n \r\nGood morning Mr. Cate,\r\n \r\nJust to let you know, we have not received the jacket yet.  Is there a problem?\r\n \r\nThank you,\r\n \r\nAnthony and Carolyn Kaufman\r\n321-414-2796\r\n \r\n \r\n-----Original Message-----\r\n From: [ 49715@reagan.com ]( mailto:49715@reagan.com )\r\n Sent: Thursday, June 5, 2025 1:24pm\r\n To: [ dcate@nrahq.org ]( mailto:dcate@nrahq.org )\r\n Subject: NRA Jacket\r\n\r\nMr. Cate,\r\n \r\nRe:  Jacket for Anthony Kaufman, Member # 19759113\r\n \r\nPlease find, attached at the end of this email, a photo of our check #566 in the amount of $250.00 for the jacket in question.  The check has been processed through our bank and the funds have been received by the NRA.\r\n \r\nWe hope this fulfills all issues related to the shipment of this jacket.\r\n \r\nThanking you in advance,\r\n \r\nAnthony and Carolyn Kaufman\r\n321-414-2796\r\n \r\n \r\n\r\n\r\nMr. and Mrs. Kaufman,\r\n \r\nMy name is Devin, and I’m the NRA Member Services Manager. Our EVP/CEO Doug Hamlin tasked me with looking into the situation described in your letter.\r\n \r\nWe don’t have a record of a call on January 14th. However, we did later receive an offer reply from you in the mail, which I’ve attached in this email, authorizing a $250 contribution and selecting the 1871 Jacket in size Large as a gift. When attempting to process that, the Discover card you provided was declined. This resulted in an open invoice being created, with the jacket on hold awaiting a valid payment. This is what led to the letters you later received thanking you for your pledge and asking for payment information.\r\n \r\nI was able to listen to a recording of the call made on March 10th, and the reason our representative could not find the order is because she was only looking at Carolyn’s membership file, while the order is under Anthony’s. I understand the confusion and frustration that would come from that, and I do apologize.\r\n \r\nAs far as the jacket, it is still on hold for you. We will just need a valid payment for the pledged $250 contribution. To do this, you can call 800-672-3888 and provide Anthony’s membership number, 19759113. That way, the representative will immediately see the open invoice and be able to apply the payment to it, which will then trigger the jacket being shipped to you. Please feel free to reply to this email if you have any additional questions or concerns.\r\n \r\nThank you,\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDevin Cate\r\nManager, Member Services\r\n Membership Division\r\nT (703) 397-3897\r\nE [ dcate@nrahq.org ]( mailto:dcate@nrahq.org )\r\n \r\n\r\nNational Rifle Association | 11250 Waples Mill Rd, Fairfax, VA 22030\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n "
